title: U.S. government warns of foreign intelligence threats to the space industry
summary: Companies in the U.S. space industry are being increasingly targeted by foreign intelligence operations, U.S. intelligence agencies warn.

title: Poland signs agreement to fly astronaut on Axiom Space ISS mission
summary: Poland has become the second European Space Agency member state to reach an agreement to fly an astronaut on a private mission to the International Space Station.

title: Japanese SAR company iQPS to launch with Rocket Lab after Virgin Orbit bankruptcy
summary: A Japanese firm developing a constellation of SAR satellites is the latest to turn to Rocket Lab after the bankruptcy of rival launch company Virgin Orbit.

title: Coverage Set for NASA’s SpaceX Crew-7 Events, Broadcast, Launch
summary: NASA will provide coverage of the upcoming prelaunch and launch activities for the agency’s SpaceX Crew-7 mission with astronauts to the International Space Station.
